The '''Potosí School''' refers to 17th-century [[Baroque]] artworks from [[Potosí]], the location of the Spanish colonial mint: "according to some accounts, the city was an art factory producing at least 200,000 paintings a year".<ref name="Jimenez2013">{{cite book|author=Alberto Corsin Jimenez|title=An Anthropological Trompe L'Oeil for a Common World: An Essay on the Economy of Knowledge|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dWRFAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA3|year=2013|publisher=Berghahn Books|isbn=978-0-85745-912-1|pages=3–4}}</ref>

