{{Infobox musical composition | name = Symphony No.&nbsp;4 | type = | composer = {{nowrap|[[Aulis Sallinen]]}} | image = | caption = | border = Yes | movements = 3 | dedication = | key = | catalogue = [[Opus number|Op.]]&nbsp;49 | composed = {{start date|1978}}–79 | duration = Approx. 23 minutes | premiere_date = {{start date|1979|08|09|df=y}} | premiere_location = [[Turku]], Finland | premiere_conductor = [[:fi:Pertti Pekkanen|Pertti Pekkanen]] | premiere_performers = [[Turku Philharmonic Orchestra]] }}
The '''Symphony No.&nbsp;4''', [[Opus number|Op]].&nbsp;49, is an orchestral composition by the Finnish composer [[Aulis Sallinen]], who wrote the piece from 1978–79 for a commission from the [[Turku|City of Turku]], to celebrate its 750th anniversary. The [[Turku Philharmonic Orchestra]] premiered the work on 9&nbsp;August 1979, under the direction of its principal conductor, [[:fi:Pertti Pekkanen|Pertti Pekkanen]].
== Structure == The symphony is in three movements: # Andante poco giocoso # Dona nobis pacem (''attacca'') # Finale
== Instrumentation == According to the publisher, [http://www.musicsalesclassical.com/composer/work/7938 Novello & Co], Symphony No.&nbsp;4 is scored for the following: *'''[[Woodwind section|Woodwind]]''': 3&nbsp;[[flute]]s (2&nbsp;doubling [[piccolo]]), 3&nbsp;[[oboe]]s, 3&nbsp;[[clarinet]]s in B{{music|flat}} (1&nbsp;doubling B{{music|flat}} [[bass clarinet]]), 3&nbsp;[[bassoon]]s (1&nbsp;doubling [[contrabassoon]]) *'''[[Brass section|Brass]]''': 4&nbsp;[[French horn|horn]]s in F, 3&nbsp;[[trumpet]]s in B{{music|flat}}, 3&nbsp;[[trombone]]s, 1&nbsp;[[tuba]] *'''[[Percussion section|Percussion]]''': [[timpani]], 3&nbsp;percussionists (individual instruments?) *'''[[String section|String]]s''': [[violin]]s, [[viola]]s, [[cello]]s, [[double bass]]es, [[harp]], [[celesta]]
== Recordings == To date, Symphony No.&nbsp;4 has received three recordings, the first of which is from 1984 with Okko Kamu conducting the Helsinki Philharmonic on the [[Warner Classics|Finlandia]] label. Finnish conductor [[:fi:Ari Rasilainen|Ari Rasilainen]] has also recorded the symphony as part of [[Classic Produktion Osnabrück|cpo's]] compendium of Sallinen's orchestral works. The Fourth Symphony joins the [[Symphony No. 2 (Sallinen)|Second]] (Op.&nbsp;29, 1972), the [[Horn Concerto (Sallinen)|Horn Concerto]] (Op.&nbsp;82, 2002), and ''Mauermusik'' (Op.&nbsp;7, 1963) on the third volume of the cpo series.
